name: SandCrabs
description:
Deborah Gaventa Brown (1954-2021) is a Yale trained abstract painter and multimedia artist. StoneCrabs is a beautiful interpretation of how your claws can grip the sand while the waves pull you out to sea, then back to land. You rest in between give and take - just like being a Mother. 

Deborah passed in 2021. Her family hopes that by minting NFTs of her paintings, they can share her legacy in new art forms while allowing collectors to own a piece of her imagination.
